  "body": "### Version Information\r\n--\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nThe example contract at:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/vyper/blob/master/examples/tokens/ERC20.vy\r\n\r\nWith vyper automatically generating getter methods for public state variables we could rename the state variable `balances` to `balanceOf`, declare it `public` and remove the `balanceOf()` method.\r\n\r\n#### Rational\r\nIf we view the example contracts as educational material, we could use this chance to introduce people to the vyper feature of automatically generating getters for public state variables.\r\n\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n* change line 10 to: `balanceOf: public(map(address, uint256))`\r\n\r\n* remove lines 37 - 45\r\n\r\n* add a comment above line 10:\r\n```\r\n# NOTE: By declaring `balanceOf` as public, vyper automatically generates a 'balanceOf()' getter \r\n#       method to allow access to account balances.\r\n#       The _KeyType will become a required parameter for the getter and it will return _ValueType.\r\n#       See: https://vyper.readthedocs.io/en/v0.1.0-beta.8/types.html?highlight=getter#mappings\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Cute Animal Picture\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10925195/52534823-927ae900-2d46-11e9-86aa-8b3711a42c6f.png)\r\n\r\n",
